WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.589 --> 00:00:03.172
(gentle music)

00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:15.330
- So through the experiences
with the user group

00:00:15.330 --> 00:00:18.520
and some of the videos we've seen online

00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:23.520
of people using X3 sometimes
they like to invent

00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:26.180
their own way of using it.

00:00:26.180 --> 00:00:28.800
I wanna strongly discourage this

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:32.830
because every movement was
really well thought out

00:00:32.830 --> 00:00:34.823
and let me give you some examples.

00:00:35.965 --> 00:00:40.430
When somebody hooks their X3 around a door

00:00:40.430 --> 00:00:44.160
and has discovered a new
way to do tricep pushdowns

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:47.920
or something like that
what they don't realize

00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:51.350
is when they throw a band
around a door they might

00:00:51.350 --> 00:00:54.040
be putting 200 pounds of downward force,

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:56.493
300 pounds of downward force on that door.

00:00:57.450 --> 00:01:01.774
Not only could they tear
the door off of their home

00:01:01.774 --> 00:01:05.850
they might end up with
that door catapulted

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:10.660
by the force created by
the band into their face.

00:01:10.660 --> 00:01:14.750
So X3 is self-contained for a reason.

00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:17.840
Incredible forces in those bands, in fact,

00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:21.260
when I do a deadlift with the Elite Band

00:01:23.660 --> 00:01:27.230
because I'm six feet tall
it's 615 pounds for me.

00:01:27.230 --> 00:01:29.467
There's an app that
calculates that for you.

00:01:31.550 --> 00:01:36.550
Now you wanna do the
movements that are recommended

00:01:37.630 --> 00:01:39.470
and in the training program.

00:01:39.470 --> 00:01:43.103
Anything other than
that you don't wanna do.

00:01:44.144 --> 00:01:48.560
I just wanna make that hard
recommendation for everybody.

00:01:48.560 --> 00:01:53.560
Now I think part of why
people wanna customize things

00:01:55.460 --> 00:01:57.700
is because they'll look at a body builder

00:01:57.700 --> 00:02:00.080
and a body builder does
30 different movements

00:02:01.650 --> 00:02:06.650
to complete their A/B split
workout or something like that.

00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:10.600
Body builders do a lot of things that are,

00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:15.260
I'll be nice, nonsensical and repetitive

00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:20.260
but I can't explain why they
do that other than they think

00:02:20.850 --> 00:02:23.070
they're getting a lot of specialization

00:02:23.070 --> 00:02:26.540
but we have professional
body builders using X3

00:02:26.540 --> 00:02:30.470
only doing the recommended protocol,

00:02:30.470 --> 00:02:33.120
exactly what the program states to do,

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:37.030
and amazingly enough they're
stimulating every muscle

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:40.820
'cause remember there are
primary engagement muscles

00:02:40.820 --> 00:02:41.680
like the pectorals.

00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:43.540
You can consciously contract your pectoral

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:44.930
when you move your arm forward.

00:02:44.930 --> 00:02:46.924
You can consciously
engage your bicep when you

00:02:46.924 --> 00:02:51.924
bring your arm toward your face
but there are other muscles

00:02:52.360 --> 00:02:54.130
that are stabilization muscles.

00:02:54.130 --> 00:02:57.270
You don't really thing about
contracting your obliques

00:02:57.270 --> 00:03:01.320
or your quadratus muscles,
and they are here and here,

00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:04.860
but you engage them
constantly when doing X3

00:03:04.860 --> 00:03:08.410
and you're developing them also
because they're stabilizers.

00:03:08.410 --> 00:03:09.270
You don't think about them.

00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:11.520
They just engage when you
need to be stabilized.

00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:14.340
When you need to be stabilized
with a weight they engage.

00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:18.240
When you need to be stabilized
through variable resistance,

00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:22.710
with X3, it's an even greater
weight so you're stimulating

00:03:22.710 --> 00:03:25.020
them to an even greater degree.

00:03:25.020 --> 00:03:30.020
So please try not to invent
your own way of doing this.

00:03:31.210 --> 00:03:35.550
Nothing is recommended other
than what is in the program.

00:03:35.550 --> 00:03:38.580
Now that doesn't mean
the somebody won't come

00:03:38.580 --> 00:03:39.670
up with an idea.

00:03:39.670 --> 00:03:44.460
Email me, email the company
and we won't add something

00:03:44.460 --> 00:03:49.460
later on but I'd say
roughly 500 different ideas

00:03:52.160 --> 00:03:55.100
have come our way and all of them were bad

00:03:55.100 --> 00:03:59.393
so let's just stick to the
program as recommended.

